reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a beautiful dress. We bought it to use for Christmas pictures. My oldest daughter wore this and my sons wore jeans and navy colored sweater vests. It was absolutely perfect for our Christmas pictures. It has also washed well and appears to be well made!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute but runs small
reviews.reviewText: Cute but runs small in bust. The smocking in the top makes it tight. Also, not a very soft material and light weight. I would recommend sizing up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Sizing is awkward
reviews.reviewText: I am not really sure what is going on with the sizing on this dress. The length is great for a modest look as well as the neckline, since this is a dress you can wear to match your daughter. The colors are also perfect for a fall or holiday style. Normally I wear an XXL, but I have also been losing weight and wanted to make sure this dress wouldn't be too tight, therefore I elected to stick with an XXL. The elastic back allows for getting the dress on overhead without issue, though I prefer a zipper back closure. The chest area is my biggest complaint as it is way too tight for someone with large breasts and did not allow for any natural curviture. The waistline was also awkwardly placed as I couldn't tell if it was meant to land at my waist or under the breast line since it landed about halfway between the two. The material is stiff which not only restricts the chest area, but makes it difficult to take off without assistance. I did like how the dress was flowy below the waist area. I do have a long torso, but considering the length of the dress, I can't confidently say this is sized for someone with a shorter torso. The material is thin but appears to be of good quality material.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality Light Dress
reviews.reviewText: I am 5'4" 230lbs. Ordered the 2XL. This is a nice looking dress with great cut and fits well. There is still a bit of bunching in the chest/neck line but that's normal for me with one pieces (I do not have the bust to match my over all size.) The fabric is solid (no see through) but nice and lightweight with quality seams. Over all great fall dress. Might be a little cold for winter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Low back, not super flattering
reviews.reviewText: The dress is a nice idea---matching with the family. However the adult dress is not that flattering, and the back went down much lower than I was expecting. The fabric feels cheap.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for teaching
reviews.reviewText: I got this dress to not only match my daughter but to wear while I teach and I love the print and pattern of it. I got a medium and I am in between a medium and a small with a larger bust. I felt like everything fits well except for around my neck. The square top came up a tad high which caused the straps to sag. I gave it 4 stars because I got this dress for $16.95 but the tag said $74.99. The quality of the fabric does not remind me of a $75 dress. The fabric will definitely need ironed or steamed after washing and wearing. Almost reminds me of a dress shirt fabric but more cotton-y feeling

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice dress
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my daughter as a potential holiday outfit. She’s a bit fussy about how her clothes fit so I was happy to find this is a nice simple cotton dress. It has a stretchy panel in the back to help make it more fitted. The colors are very classic looking and go with a variety of accent colors. The skirt is a nice length and fullness.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Why is this dress noisy?!
reviews.reviewText: I was a little worried about sizing because the dress is cotton so I ordered one size larger. I do NOT think that was a mistake. I have some wiggle room but not as much as one whole size up. I also don’t like tight clothes.I really like the pattern and color. However I wasn’t expecting it to be noisy! The closest thing I can compare it to would be a cheap waterproof mattress protector (or a plastic bag). It’s really strange and something you would think the manufacturer would have noticed!I think the cut is attractive as is the color choice. I just wish it wasn’t so loud. It’s really awkward and I won’t wear it out of the house because of this.
